  Description:  

Exclusive NEW adult animated emoticons & display images/avatars

These images can be used as:

>> Buddy Icons in AOL AIM Messenger
>> Avatars for Yahoo Messenger
>> Avatars and emoticons for MSN Messenger
>> Avatars Images for Skype
>> Avatars in Google Talk


=============
MSN MESSENGER
=============

To Install Avatars into MSN Messenger, follow these steps;
    1. Open the main Messenger window.
    2. Click the ?Tools&#039; menu and select ?Change Display Picture&#039; 
    3. Click ?Browse&#039; in the My Display Picture dialogue box 
    4. Select the emoticon you want to add 
    5. Click ?ok&#039; 

To install emoticons into MSN Messenger, follow these steps;
    1. Open the main Messenger window.
    2. Click the ?Tools&#039; menu and select ?My Emoticons&#039; 
    3. Click ?Create&#039; in the My Emoticons dialogue box 
    4. Click ?Find image&#039; and select the emoticon you want to add 
    5. Type a shortcut key to assign to this emoticon 
    6. Type a name for your emoticon 
    7. Click ?ok&#039; 


===============
YAHOO MESSENGER
===============

To Install Avatars into YAHOO, follow these steps;
    1. Open your Yahoo Instant Messenger buddy list and click on the smiley face
       (or your old display picture) to the left of your username at the top of the 
       buddy list. In the smiley face menu, select on "Choose a Picture...".
    2. In the "My Pictures" window, click on "Browse...". 
    3. Select the avatar you want to add 
    4. Click ?ok&#039; 


=====
SKYPE
=====

To Install Avatars into SKYPE, follow these steps;
    1. Open Skype and go to ?File? on the menu. Select ?Your Personal Profile? 
       and open up your Skype Personal Profile.
    2. You&#039;ll see the display picture box at the bottom left of your profile screen. 
       To upload a Photo you that you already have saved on your computer, just click 
       browse and import the image you want. 
    3. Click ?ok&#039; 


===========
GOOGLE TALK
===========

To Install Avatars into Google Talk, follow these steps;
    1. Open the Google Talk buddy list and click on the picture to the right of your 
       name near the top of the buddy list window. If you do not see the picture selector, 
       upgrade to the newest version of Google Talk.
    2. Click on "More pictures..." at the bottom of the icon selector, navigate to where 
       you saved your avatar, select the avatar, and click "Open"
    3. Your avatar is now installed. Hover your mouse over your name to see it full size. 


=================
AOL AIM MESSENGER
=================

To Install Avatars into AIM Messenger, follow these steps;
    1. Go to your AIM Triton buddy list and go to the Tools menu, select Settings (F7).
    2. Click on Expressions from the list on the left. Click the Browse button under 
       the buddy icon in the top right corner.
    3. Navigate to the icon you previously saved to your hard drive, click on the name of 
       the icon, and click Open.
    4. Click Ok on the copyright warning and Save in the preferences window to save your changes.



=======
MYSPACE
=======

To Install Avatars into MySpace, follow these steps;
    1. Go to the MySpace homepage, click on "Home" and log in, if necessary. 
       Click on "Upload / Change Photos"
    2. Go to the "Upload Photo" box part way down the page and click on "Browse...".
    3. Find the avatar or icon on your computer and click "Open"
    4. Next, click on "Upload" to send the image to MySpace. Please note that it my appear 
       like nothing happened after the upload is complete. Wait 30 seconds then scroll down 
       the page to see your uploaded avatar.
    5. Finally, if you have more than one image, you need to tell it which one you want 
       to appear next to your name. Click on "-Set as default-" to change the photo shown 
       on your MySpace page. That&#039;s it!
